You can draw the structure of an addition polymer from the structure of its
monomer. Here’s how to do this:
1.Start by drawing the two alkene carbons, replace the double bond with a
single bond and add an extra single bond to each of the carbons.

You may be given a polymer and asked to draw the monomer that makes
it. All you have to do is take the bit of the polymer that repeats, remove
the bonds from either side and add a double bond into it.
